disable firewall: sudo /usr/libexec/ApplicationFirewall/socketfilterfw --setglobalstate off
enable firewall: sudo /usr/libexec/ApplicationFirewall/socketfilterfw --setglobalstate on

FLASK_APP=app.py flask run --host=0.0.0.0 --port=8080

In order:
DEPLOYING:
-get online
-get pin of current location working
-fix stupid white icon appearing when editing in profile
-upon sign up take directly to home, no need to login
-pop ups saying if incorrect password, etc for quality of life
-confirm information popup once upload is completed
-upload in mass, manage group information
-find way to make uploading faster, add multiple
-drag and drop or select file choices
-save just the frame that is being analyzed, so user can view whats on camera but minimizes space
**instead of viewing video for each upload, have it all in the popup on initial upload. User edits and checks stuff
and if all is good, puts uploads in upload history and deletes video.

MOBILE:
-build react version afterwards, make another bucket
-connect that to same ec2 instance

AI:
-train ai off of rest of footage
-also look at other ways to effectively train it


